/-!
# `S`-units of Dedekind domains: the `S`-valuation short exact sequence

Let `K` be the fraction field of a Dedekind domain `R` and `S` a set of primes in the height-one
spectrum. The group of `S`-units `Set.unit S K` (defined in
`Mathlib/RingTheory/DedekindDomain/SInteger.lean`) fits in a short exact sequence
`1 вҶ’ рқ’Ә_K^Г— вҶ’ рқ’Ә_{K,S}^Г— вҶ’ вҠ•_{v вҲҲ S} в„Ө`, where the second map records the `v`-adic valuations at the
primes of `S`. From it this file proves the `SInteger.lean` *"Future work"*: the **finite
generation** of `S`-units and **Dirichlet's `S`-unit theorem** (the exact rank `rank рқ’Ә_K^Г— + |S|`,
and for a number field `(rвӮҒ + rвӮӮ - 1) + |S|`).

## Main definitions

* `Set.unitValuation`: the `S`-valuation map `рқ’Ә_{K,S}^Г— вҶ’* (вҶҘS вҶ’ Multiplicative в„Ө)`,
  `u вҶҰ (v(u))_{v вҲҲ S}`.

## Main statements

* `Set.unitValuation_ker`: the kernel of `Set.unitValuation` is the `вҲ…`-units `Set.unit вҲ… K`, i.e.
  the units with trivial valuation at *every* prime вҖ” the units `рқ’Ә_K^Г—` of the base ring.
* `Set.unit_fg`: **finite generation of `S`-units** вҖ” when `S` is finite and the `вҲ…`-units `рқ’Ә_K^Г—`
  are finitely generated (e.g. a number field, by Dirichlet's unit theorem), `рқ’Ә_{K,S}^Г—` is finitely
  generated. The image of `unitValuation` is a subgroup of the (finitely generated) free group
  `вҶҘS вҶ’ в„Ө`, the kernel is `рқ’Ә_K^Г—`, and an extension of finitely generated by finitely generated is
  finitely generated.
* `Set.finrank_le`: **upper bound on the `S`-unit rank** вҖ” `rank рқ’Ә_{K,S}^Г— вүӨ rank рқ’Ә_K^Г— + |S|`, via
  rank-nullity (`finrank_eq_add_finrank_range`) and `finrank (range) вүӨ |S|`.
* `Set.finrank_range`: the image of `unitValuation` has full `в„Ө`-rank `|S|`, when `S` and
  `ClassGroup R` are finite. For each `v вҲҲ S`, `v.asIdeal ^ (orderOf [v.asIdeal])` is principal (the
  class group is finite), giving an `S`-unit with `unitValuation` supported at `v`; the `|S|` such
  images are `в„Ө`-linearly independent.
* `Set.finrank_eq`: **Dirichlet's `S`-unit theorem (rank form)** вҖ” `rank рқ’Ә_{K,S}^Г— = rank рқ’Ә_K^Г— +
  |S|`, when `S` and `ClassGroup R` are finite.
* `Set.unit_finrank_numberField`: **Dirichlet's `S`-unit theorem for number fields** вҖ” for a number
  field `K`, `rank рқ’Ә_{K,S}^Г— = (rвӮҒ + rвӮӮ - 1) + |S|` (`NumberField.Units.rank K + |S|`).

Two reusable lemmas are proved en route: `CommGroup.fg_of_fg_ker_of_fg_range` (a commutative group
with finitely generated kernel and range under a hom is finitely generated) and its module analogue
`Module.Finite.of_fg_ker_of_fg_range`. `Set.unitEmptyEquivUnits` identifies the `вҲ…`-units with `RЛЈ`.

## References

* [D Marcus, *Number Fields*][marcus1977number]
* [J W S Cassels, A FrГ¶hlich, *Algebraic Number Theory*][cassels1967algebraic]
* [J Neukirch, *Algebraic Number Theory*][Neukirch1992]

## Tags

S-unit, S-units, Dirichlet S-unit theorem, finite generation, valuation
-/

